headline.main: Dulles Formulated and Conducted U. S. Foreign Policy for More Than Six Years; TENURE AROUSED MIXED APPRAISAL Admirers Hailed His Tactics in Diplomacy but Critics Scored Inflexibility CABINET IN HIS HERITAGE His Grandfather and Uncle Had Served the Nation as Secretaries of State

snippet: For six years John Foster Dulles dominated both the making and the conduct of United States foreign policy. In the realm of foreign affairs he was President Eisenhower's chief adviser, his chief representative on Capitol Hill and his chief agent a...
